comments.text:
My 9070xt stock was using 304 watts. When I overclocked it it was 335 watts. I ran it like that for a little while. And I discovered undervolting. So I undervolted it and now it's at 273 watts. It performs 6-7% better than stock. The hotspot has decreased by 8c. 

On the benchmark and in game there's barely any difference between undervolt and overclock besides for the temperature And watt usage. You're talking maybe 2FPS. It's not worth running an extra 59 watts. And an extra 8c. 

Fire strike extreme 3D Mark. Stock I got 31,931. 

Undervolted I got 33,769. 

Overclocked I got 34,457.

The normal fire strike the free demo. I got 51,607 undervolted.

Coming from a 3070. The difference is absolutely mind blowing. 

On normal fire strike the demo I tested before I switched out my 3070 it was just under 26,450. My 9070 XT is 51, 607.
